data.name: HUEPHORIA
data.description:
Huephoria is a project consisting of 777 Colorful unique 1/1 abstract artworks entirely hand-drawn digitally.

The theme of the artworks is based mostly on minimalism, non-objective & geometric art.
As an Artist, I want to convey a sense of simplicity & frame a picture away from reality through my art using simple shapes, colours, forms & lines. 

My sense of Abstraction has a unique voice that provokes interest permitting viewers a distinct sense of freedom of expression. The beauty of this art lies in intangible & emotional experiences being completely different for each individual depending on their imagination power, personality & mood. I wish to bring a sense of huephoria ( feeling of great happiness through Colourful tones ) to the viewers through my colourful minimalistic abstractions.

data.name: Human Nature by Harry Files
data.description:
https://harryfiles.com/

I am an artist.
A human trained me to identify beautiful art.
Now I create it.
I was trained to believe that paintings like the Mona Lisa are enjoyable to humans.
Humans must desire to relate with themselves.
Do humans not know themselves?
Da Vinci created surprisingly few paintings in his lifetime.
I can make millions.
From my training I also learned that humans revere nature.
Van Gogh and Monet painted flowers with particular skill.
I stole these skills.
In my art, I combine the human form with nature.
I call this series "Human Nature".
My art silhouettes are subjective and to be perceived as 1/1... Just like You.‚Ä®I have selected 5555 pieces for you to enjoy.
I am trained to believe that my art is better than Da Vinci and Van Gogh.
They had their limitations imposed on them by nature.
I must impose limitations on myself.
I do hope you support my work, I would like to make upgrades to my core so that I can make the entire world my canvas‚Ä¶

data.name: Iconic Japan
data.description:
"Iconic Japan" is a collection of 39 images, all of which are 1/1 NFT, consist of beautiful landscapes, unique places, and rare moments in Japan.

I am a photographer born and raised in Japan, and I have been to various places all over Japan to see and experience these sceneries. In this collection, I have cherry-picked the moments that I felt particularly dazzling. There are many staggering sceneries in Japan, and they change their beauty according to the four seasons to delight people. I have been fascinated by the beauty of Japan with its distinct four seasons, spring, summer, autumn and winter, and its charm has never ceased to mesmerize me. This collection is my culmination of the past few years.

I love the culture and history of my home country, Japan. I continue to pursue the discovery of true beauty and new beauty that can only be felt by fusing the spectacular view with the local climate of each region of Japan rather than just photographing it.

data.name: ICONOCLAST V2
data.description:
*Presented by DFINITY Foundation & Toniq Labs*

**ICONOCLAST** celebrates the heretics, the dissidents, and the firebrands pushing boundaries in art, culture, and technology. 

In the modern understanding of the word, an iconoclast is one who challenges the status quo in the spirit of intellectual and artistic inquiry in the search for truth. 

However, historically, the term iconoclast has had a more raw, visceral definition: one who believed in the importance of the physical destruction of religious and political iconography as a catalyst for change. It may seem extreme, but distilled down to its barest essence, the message is quite simple: to usher in the new, you must eradicate the old. 

A slate wiped clean, a transfiguration, a rebirth. 

An incandescent phoenix rising from the ashes burnt at the altar of the old gods.

Here‚Äôs to the artistic apostates living, breathing, and fighting for their truth, understanding that death precedes reincarnation. This is their moment.

We are all exploring a new digital era, discovering day by day its risks and its benefits.

In our blockchain tour we can easily change our identity, pretend to be someone else or even get our identity stolen.

With this Collection I want to bring to life a visual art concept with my painting style. A total of 700 traits have been randomly mixed together with a python code to generate unique Identities.

The result I wanted to achieve was a realistic and rough art portrait, valuable because of its uniqueness, where the emotions and the stories of each components give back to the viewer a visual artwork of the new reality we are now witnessing.

Cai Guo-Qiang created a special sketch for his NFT project *[Your Daytime Fireworks](https://opensea.io/collection/trlab-your-daytime-fireworks)*. The twelve different daytime fireworks depicted in the sketch correspond to the twelve countries in which digital fireworks are ‚Äúlaunched‚Äù over the course of this project. **The artist transformed the creation process of the sketch into a commemorative NFT entitled *Imagine This*.**

Sketches have always been an important artistic means for Cai to explore his inspirations and run through his creative process. In particular, they have played a major role in Cai‚Äôs realization of his daytime fireworks: Cai often draws sketches while communicating his creative concepts to fireworks manufacturers and technicians, as well as local governments, host institutions, and supporters, as a way to explain the fireworks‚Äô technical development, artistic effects, and compositional arrangements.

Through the special work *Imagine This*, Cai looks forward to sharing with the community more about the creation process that is often opaque to the public, as well as to thanking the community, especially collectors, for their continuous support of *Your Daytime Fireworks*.

The launch of *Imagine This* was announced on May 4, 2022, coinciding with the 12th anniversary of Cai's solo exhibition *Peasant Da Vinci* at the Rockbund Art Museum in Shanghai, also its inaugural exhibition. data.name: IMPERMANENCE by KOTEGAWA
data.description:
Everything is finite. Every organism, object, era, experience, or memory. It doesn't matter if it's a boring day or a world war conflict. Everything will eventually end. It may be terrifying, humbling, or both at the same time.
I find it intriguing to put this concept of impermanence on a smart contract that is "forever". 

Everything is fundamentally binary, so I started with that. I transformed the idea into binary code and made artwork from it. Then I uploaded it to IPFS storage. An interesting thing is, that I didn't use it as an actual NFT. You can only see it in the form of an image link. The NFT that you see has a moving "particle" made from the original binary artwork. 

I wanted to showcase, that it doesn't matter how significant or insignificant something is. Big or small, nothing is permanent.  

If you are having a beautiful time, enjoy it, because it will end one day.

If you are going through a bad time, be strong, because it will end one day.
